{
  "doc_id": "4654",
  "text": "One of the principal goals of advanced restorative dental treatment, including endodontics and implant placement, is to improve the quality of life for patients. A survey of patients conducted by Gatten et al. [CITATION_1] showed a high degree of satisfaction with both endodontic and implant treatment. Factors considered by patients to be important were overall general health, costs, perception of treatment and its outcomes and subsequent dental follow-up. The patients were content with the treatment they had received but they were anxious to save their natural dentition whenever possible. Good masticatory function also contributes to quality of life. One study has shown that endodontically treated natural teeth may provide more effective chewing than implant retained restorations.",
